items.name: Maria Whittaker (1987-90 era - LORA)
items.description:
Shivam Dreambooth LORA conversion of British 1980s/90s glamor model Maria Whittaker, using 80 ref images and 1980 (real) reg images, for 8,000 steps. The period covered is around 1987-1990.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

This model may well produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered in negative prompts.

items.name: Yamagumo (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Yamagumo from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 97 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.8], (1 - 0.65)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

YamagumoKC, (white) shirt, (suspenders) skirt, (green) hairband, (pleated) skirt, (grey) skirt, (black) socks, shoes

Special outfits

YamagumoLeyteKC, (white) shirt, (grey) jacket, (green) hairband, (pleated) skirt, (grey) skirt, (black) socks, shoes

-ponytail, braid, (single) braid, sidelocks, (white) ponytail band
-(long sleeves) jacket, (sailor collar) jacket, (grey) sailor collar
-(black) kneehighs

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-(single) braid, scrunchie, sidelocks, (green) bowtie, (plaid) bowtie
-(short sleeves) shirt, (suspenders) shirt, (collared) shirt, school uniform
-arm warmers

-grey eyes

items.name: Peta Jensen (JG)
items.description:
Peta Jensen is an American retired adult actress and model.

120-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (abc0rnish:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Megan Fox SDXL LoRA
items.description:
10000 steps. Trained in local Kohya install. 4090. Trained on DreamShaper XL1.0 Alpha2. I followed SECourses SDXL LoRA Guide.

Most images were on DreamShaper XL A2 in A1111/ComfyUI. Hi-res fix with R-ESRGAN (1.25) and 0.2-0.4 denoising strength. Upscaled using "4x_NickelbackFS_72000_G" or "4x_NMKD-Siax_200k"

Help me out by liking and following me to see my new models. Submit some of your outputs and post your SUGGESTIONS in the comments below. I am pacing around 6-10 models weekly depending on my actual job workload. If you liked my models and want to support the work I do you can buy me a pizza!

List of upcoming LoRAs I intend to do as well as what I am currently working on.

items.name: Noir (NIKKE) LoRA
items.description:
Noir from Goddess of Victory: Nikke

Our beloved timid lucky bunny.

In order to spawn a Noir of your own, use these tags.

Character Tags

noir, huge breasts, wide hips, narrow waist, thick thighs, very long hair,

Default Outfit Tags

leotard, rabbit ears, rabbit tail, highleg leotard, wrist cuffs, detached collar, black bow, pantyhose, fishnets

Author Notes

This lora is fairly flexible and provides an accurate character representation most of the time.

Only tags relating to physical characteristics such as hair/eye/skin color have been pruned.

Do note that body tags were not pruned.

You will need to specify tags such as bust size and so on.

This is to enable better flexibility with other loras and checkpoints.

You can even prompt Noirs of different sizes.

-

So why did I make this?

I couldn't find a good lora of Noir that wasn't fried, so I decided to bake my own.

64 DIM fp16 lora trained on clip skip 2 with 175 images at 4 repeats at 1024 resolution.

Trained on NAI, compatible with any sort of anime model mix based on NAI.

items.name: Sophia Loren (1958-65 era - LORA)
items.description:
Medium-quality Shivam Dreambooth LORA conversion of Italian actress and sex symbol Sophia Loren, using 188 ref images and 1400 (real) reg images, for 12,000 steps.

Why it's larger than usual. It can be very rewarding to use, but this is a tricky model, and I therefore didn't FP16 the Kohya conversion - I didn't want to over-slim the weights in this case. It's not the most resilient model I did.

To get a generation of the younger version, put the word young in front of the key prompt, and use brackets to control the degree of youth.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

This model may well produce subject-accurate NSFW output unless countered in negative prompts.

items.name: Celina Ralph
items.description:
Celina Ralph is a British model. I'm pretty sure she will become one of the UK's top models in the years to come.

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (c3lralph:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Giulia Penna
items.description:
Giulia Penna is a famous Italian pop singer, whose talent and enchanting voice have captured the hearts of the audience. Born on May 9, 1992, in Italy, she grew up with a passion for music, which led her to pursue a career in the entertainment industry.

Over the years, Giulia has established herself as a versatile artist, being both a singer and a songwriter. Her songs, such as "Odio L'Estate" and "Fuori Ã¨ giÃ  Natale," released in 2016, have achieved tremendous success, propelling her career to new heights. Her music, a subtle blend of catchy pop sounds and poignant lyrics, has earned her a devoted fan base worldwide.

In addition to her musical talents, Giulia has also demonstrated her skills as a performer on stage. Her concerts are renowned for their captivating energy and the connection she establishes with her audience.

In 2014, Giulia reached a significant milestone in her career by winning the prestigious Giam Academy competition. This victory provided her with increased visibility in the industry and solidified her position as an emerging artist to watch closely.

Outside of music, Giulia is also a beloved personality in the entertainment world. She has had the opportunity to pose for photos alongside other celebrities, including Italian actress Ludovica Bizzaglia in October 2016, further enhancing her fame.

With her undeniable talent, charismatic presence, and dedication to her art, Giulia Penna continues to inspire and captivate her audience, hinting at a promising future for this rising star in Italian music.
